    <section class="article-page">
        <div class="article-meta">DECEMBER 2024 · 3 MIN READ</div>
        <h1>Why do some people give up and others don’t?</h1>
        <p>Every entrepreneur has failed. Even I have, even though I am very young (16) and barely an entrepreneur. I’ve struggled with over seven businesses that I gave up on. But why did I?</p>
        <p>And how am I now sure that I'll never give up anymore? The answer lies in mindset, perseverance, and learning from failure. People who don’t give up often have a strong sense of purpose, a growth mindset, and the habit of taking consistent action even when results aren’t immediate.</p>
        <p>Another factor is how you perceive failure. Successful people treat failure as feedback, not as a dead end. They analyze what went wrong, make adjustments, and try again. Meanwhile, others may feel discouraged and stop entirely.</p>
        <p>Building resilience is also key. It’s not about being fearless; it’s about feeling fear or doubt and choosing to move forward anyway. Over time, this builds confidence, competence, and an unshakable determination.</p>
        <p>In conclusion, giving up is a choice, but persistence is a habit that can be cultivated. By focusing on growth, learning from mistakes, and maintaining a clear purpose, anyone can develop the mindset to keep going when others quit.</p>
    </section>

